briefdescription.para: Specify whether the matrix is to be transposed or not.

detaileddescription.para: The rocsparse_operation indicates the operation performed with the given matrix.

The rocsparse_index_base indicates the index base of the indices. For a given rocsparse_mat_descr, the rocsparse_index_base can be set using rocsparse_set_mat_index_base(). The current rocsparse_index_base of a matrix can be obtained by rocsparse_get_mat_index_base().

The rocsparse_matrix_type indices the type of a matrix. For a given rocsparse_mat_descr, the rocsparse_matrix_type can be set using rocsparse_set_mat_type(). The current rocsparse_matrix_type of a matrix can be obtained by rocsparse_get_mat_type().

briefdescription.para: Indicates if the diagonal entries are unity.

detaileddescription.para: The rocsparse_diag_type indicates whether the diagonal entries of a matrix are unity or not. If rocsparse_diag_type_unit is specified, all present diagonal values will be ignored. For a given rocsparse_mat_descr, the rocsparse_diag_type can be set using rocsparse_set_mat_diag_type(). The current rocsparse_diag_type of a matrix can be obtained by rocsparse_get_mat_diag_type().

The rocsparse_fill_mode indicates whether the lower or the upper part is stored in a sparse triangular matrix. For a given rocsparse_mat_descr, the rocsparse_fill_mode can be set using rocsparse_set_mat_fill_mode(). The current rocsparse_fill_mode of a matrix can be obtained by rocsparse_get_mat_fill_mode().

briefdescription.para: Specify where the operation is performed on.

detaileddescription.para: The rocsparse_action indicates whether the operation is performed on the full matrix, or only on the sparsity pattern of the matrix.

detaileddescription.para: The rocsparse_hyb_partition type indicates how the hybrid format partitioning between COO and ELL storage formats is performed.

The rocsparse_analysis_policy specifies whether gathered analysis data should be re-used or not. If meta data from a previous e.g. rocsparse_csrilu0_analysis() call is available, it can be re-used for subsequent calls to e.g. rocsparse_csrsv_analysis() and greatly improve performance of the analysis function.

Handle to the rocSPARSE library context queue.

detaileddescription.para: The rocSPARSE handle is a structure holding the rocSPARSE library context. It must be initialized using rocsparse_create_handle() and the returned handle must be passed to all subsequent library function calls. It should be destroyed at the end using rocsparse_destroy_handle().

The rocSPARSE matrix descriptor is a structure holding all properties of a matrix. It must be initialized using rocsparse_create_mat_descr() and the returned descriptor must be passed to all subsequent library calls that involve the matrix. It should be destroyed at the end using rocsparse_destroy_mat_descr().

The rocSPARSE HYB matrix structure holds the HYB matrix. It must be initialized using rocsparse_create_hyb_mat() and the returned HYB matrix must be passed to all subsequent library calls that involve the matrix. It should be destroyed at the end using rocsparse_destroy_hyb_mat().

briefdescription.para: Info structure to hold all matrix meta data.

detaileddescription.para: The rocSPARSE matrix info is a structure holding all matrix information that is gathered during analysis routines. It must be initialized using rocsparse_create_mat_info() and the returned info structure must be passed to all subsequent library calls that require additional matrix information. It should be destroyed at the end using rocsparse_destroy_mat_info().
